org.askalon.jlibcloud.compute.types

Interface Arg

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArgImpl

    public interface Arg
    Represents an (command line) argument. An argument is a int, float or String value. In Python it's possible to put String and int values into a single map.

    Example usecase:

    dict = {'key1':'strVal', 'key2':1}

    def python_method(dict);

    public python_method_wrapper(Map dict);

    Author:
    root
